content:
Previous NZ Labour gov't wasn't great on protecting animals either. Department of Conservation (DOC) OKed killing 46 species of wildlife - including protected kiwi - during construction of Te Ara o Te Ata Mt Messenger bypass in Taranaki. One example of DOC's inadequacy in its role.

DOC granted Waka Kotahi NZTA a Wildlife Act Authority in late 2021. It allowed the deaths of NI brown kiwi, bats, and Archey's frog during the project.
https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/500394/group-files-judicial-review-over-doc-decision-allowing-for-deaths-during-mt-messenger-project

content:
There are so many ridiculous lines in that techno-crapitalist manifesto, it's a feast for critique. Here's another course.

The medical / life-saving argument sounds like nothing that has ever been heard from the actual trailblazers of progress in medical science.

It sounds more like something that Dr Frankenstein would have said, if Shelly were writing her novel today.

It's "what if heroic medicine, but the doctor is a large language model trained on WebMD and Yahoo Answers."

content:
What was #Hamas goal with the attack?
